reviews.review: This is for the expanded universe
Amazing! Such a fantastic ending to the saga I grew up with.

Though, there are some flaws, this is an excellent final installment to the Skywalker Saga!  I loved it and am going to see it again!  Thank you JJ Abrams for pulling out a victory from the jaws of defeat!

I watched it 2 times, it was something closer to a StarWars film, but there were so many weird plot lines which came out of nowhere. I am not a fan of the last jedi, but still it exists. JJ Abrams acts almost like that movie didn't happen.  Why was there no plan or direction for this trilogy? 
Make a cohesive story over 3 films. If you don't have any ideas, use the hundreds of books that exist in the Legends. just a shame, waste of opportunity...
Disgusting fan fiction. George Lucas hates it so much he didn't go to the premiere. That says it all about this mess.

The movie is complete garbage. Although, JJ tried to fill the many plot holes left by Rian Johnson and partially succeeded in doing so but in the wake of doing so created even more egregious holes and mistakes that totally destroyed the Star Wars universe we love. If a person thinks about what they watched they will see so many issues that just donâ€™t make sense. Star Wars is really only episodes 1-6 forget about episodes 7-9. 8 and 9 are huge turds in the saga. I am really beginning to like Jar Jar Binks!

Anything is better then "The Last Jedi", the worst movie of all time. So, "The Rise of Skywalker" is better, but that's not saying much... It really doesn't take a lot of effort to be better then the worst one...
